---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Our Work — New Castle International Corp." description="A documented record of NCIC's role in building the New Castle County–Qiqihar sister city relationship and Delaware-China economic development framework.">
  <Nav />

  <section class="work-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Documented Track Record</div>
      <h1>The Work That<br>Built the Bridge</h1>
      <p class="sub">From 2014 to 2016, NCIC orchestrated a series of high-level meetings, trade delegations, and bilateral agreements between New Castle County and the city of Qiqihar, China — bringing together government officials, multinational company executives, port authority leadership, and civic leaders from both nations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CASE STUDY TIMELINE -->
  <section class="case-study">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- CHAPTER 1 -->
      <div class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-header">
          <span class="chapter-num">Chapter I</span>
          <h2>Establishing the Relationship</h2>
          <p class="chapter-date">2014 — New Castle County, Delaware</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chapter-body">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p>NCIC identified Qiqihar — a major industrial and agricultural center in northeast China — as a strategic partner for New Castle County. Working through cross-cultural business networks spanning Philadelphia's Chinatown business community and established Asian business leaders, NCIC built the introduction that would lead to a formal government-to-government agreement.</p>
            <p>In November 2014, Mayor Zhe Sun of Qiqihar led an official delegation to New Castle County, Delaware. The delegation signed the Sister City Agreement — a formal bilateral framework covering economy, trade, science, technology, culture, education, sports, and tourism.</p>
            <div class="milestone">
              <span class="milestone-date">November 2014</span>
              <span class="milestone-text">Sister City Agreement signed between New Castle County and Qiqihar, China</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <img src="/images/gallery/agreement-signing.jpg" alt="Agreement exchange between delegations" />
            <div class="img-caption">Official document exchange during the NCC-Qiqihar signing ceremony</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CHAPTER 2 -->
      <div class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-header">
          <span class="chapter-num">Chapter II</span>
          <h2>The Boardroom Sessions</h2>
          <p class="chapter-date">March 2016 — New Castle County Government Center</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chapter-body reverse">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p>NCIC convened a series of high-level meetings at the New Castle County Government Center bringing together American officials, Chinese business executives, and institutional stakeholders to advance concrete economic development opportunities.</p>
            <p>The meetings included executives from some of China's largest multinational corporations — including companies ranked among the world's top enterprises in shipping, construction, and industrial manufacturing — alongside Delaware state officials, port authority representatives, and International Longshoremen's Association leadership negotiating the future of the Port of Wilmington.</p>
            <div class="milestone">
              <span class="milestone-date">March 2016</span>
              <span class="milestone-text">Multi-session economic development summit at NCC Government Center</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <img src="/images/gallery/boardroom-full.jpg" alt="Full boardroom session with delegations" />
            <div class="img-caption">Joint session with American officials and Chinese corporate executives, NCC Government Center</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="photo-strip">
          <div class="strip-item">
            <img src="/images/gallery/boardroom-full-2.jpg" alt="Boardroom session 2" />
          </div>
          <div class="strip-item">
            <img src="/images/gallery/meeting-trio.jpg" alt="Meeting with delegation" />
          </div>
          <div class="strip-item">
            <img src="/images/gallery/meeting-winson-dan.jpg" alt="NCIC principals with delegation" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CHAPTER 3 -->
      <div class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-header">
          <span class="chapter-num">Chapter III</span>
          <h2>Access at the Highest Level</h2>
          <p class="chapter-date">March 2016 — New Castle County Government Center</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chapter-body">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p>NCIC's principals maintained direct access to New Castle County's highest levels of government — a relationship built over years of trust, results, and genuine service to the county's economic development mission.</p>
            <p>NCIC served as the trusted bridge between county government and the international business community, facilitating introductions and relationship-building that no government office could accomplish independently. This access was the foundation of the entire Delaware-China economic development initiative.</p>
            <div class="milestone">
              <span class="milestone-date">2014–2016</span>
              <span class="milestone-text">NCIC served as primary international liaison to New Castle County Executive leadership</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <img src="/images/gallery/winson-gordons-office.jpg" alt="NCIC liaison at New Castle County Government Center" />
            <div class="img-caption">NCIC's international liaison at New Castle County Government Center, 2016</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CHAPTER 4 -->
      <div class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-header">
          <span class="chapter-num">Chapter IV</span>
          <h2>The Diplomatic Exchange</h2>
          <p class="chapter-date">March 2016 — Formal Gift & Recognition Ceremony</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chapter-body reverse">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p>A formal diplomatic gift exchange was held between the Chinese delegation and Delaware leadership — a ceremony that marks the transition from initial relationship-building to sustained bilateral partnership.</p>
            <p>The exchange included senior representatives from both governments and the Chinese corporate delegation, with NCIC principals present as the facilitating organization that made the relationship possible.</p>
            <div class="milestone">
              <span class="milestone-date">March 2016</span>
              <span class="milestone-text">Formal diplomatic recognition and gift exchange ceremony</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <img src="/images/gallery/gift-exchange-trio.jpg" alt="Diplomatic gift exchange" />
            <div class="img-caption">Formal gift exchange between Chinese and American delegations</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="photo-strip one-up">
          <div class="strip-item wide">
            <img src="/images/gallery/gift-exchange-group.jpg" alt="Gift exchange group" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CHAPTER 5 -->
      <div class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-header">
          <span class="chapter-num">Chapter V</span>
          <h2>The Delegation Dinner</h2>
          <p class="chapter-date">March 2016 — Wilmington, Delaware</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chapter-body">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p>NCIC organized and hosted a delegation dinner bringing together the full complement of American and Chinese stakeholders — government officials, corporate executives, port authority leadership, and civic leaders — in an informal setting to advance relationship-building beyond the boardroom.</p>
            <p>The dinner table included US government officials, Chinese multinational executives, and Delaware community and institutional leaders — a gathering that represented the breadth of the coalition NCIC had assembled over two years of relationship-building.</p>
            <div class="milestone">
              <span class="milestone-date">March 2016</span>
              <span class="milestone-text">Multi-stakeholder delegation dinner, Wilmington — 15+ attendees across both nations</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <img src="/images/gallery/delegation-dinner.jpg" alt="Delegation dinner" />
            <div class="img-caption">Joint delegation dinner with American and Chinese leaders, Wilmington</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE BUILT -->
  <section class="built-band">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">The Outcome</div>
      <h2>What NCIC Built</h2>
      <div class="built-grid">
        <div class="built-item">
          <span class="built-num">01</span>
          <h4>A Signed Government Agreement</h4>
          <p>The formal NCC-Qiqihar Sister City Agreement — the only county-level US-China bilateral agreement in Delaware — covering economy, trade, education, culture, and tourism.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="built-item">
          <span class="built-num">02</span>
          <h4>Corporate Relationships</h4>
          <p>Direct introductions between Delaware leadership and executives from some of China's largest multinationals — including top-ranked shipping, construction, and industrial companies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="built-item">
          <span class="built-num">03</span>
          <h4>Government Access</h4>
          <p>A working relationship with the Office of the County Executive, the Delaware State Senate, the Port of Wilmington authority, and the International Longshoremen's Association.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="built-item">
          <span class="built-num">04</span>
          <h4>A Replicable Model</h4>
          <p>A proven methodology for international municipal partnership development — from initial introduction through formal agreement — now available to cities and counties across the Mid-Atlantic region.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="work-cta">
    <div class="container work-cta-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="section-label">Work With Us</div>
        <h2>Your City Could Be Next</h2>
        <p>NCIC's model is replicable. If your city, county, or institution is looking to build international economic partnerships — we know how to make it happen.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/partner" class="cta-btn">Express Interest →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
.work-hero{background:var(--navy);padding:80px 0;color:var(--offwhite);border-bottom:2px solid var(--gold)}
.work-hero h1{font-size:clamp(32px,4vw,56px);color:var(--offwhite);margin-bottom:20px;font-weight:normal;line-height:1.1}
.work-hero .sub{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#94A3B8;max-width:700px;line-height:1.8}

.case-study{padding:80px 0;background:var(--offwhite)}

.chapter{margin-bottom:96px;padding-bottom:96px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--light)}
.chapter:last-child{border-bottom:none;margin-bottom:0;padding-bottom:0}

.chapter-header{margin-bottom:48px}
.chapter-num{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.3em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:12px}
.chapter-num::before{content:'';display:block;width:24px;height:1px;background:var(--gold)}
.chapter-header h2{font-size:clamp(24px,3vw,38px);color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:normal}
.chapter-date{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.05em}

.chapter-body{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:64px;align-items:start;margin-bottom:40px}
.chapter-body.reverse{direction:rtl}
.chapter-body.reverse > *{direction:ltr}

.chapter-text p{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px}

.milestone{margin-top:32px;padding:20px 24px;background:var(--navy);display:flex;gap:20px;align-items:start}
.milestone-date{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);white-space:nowrap;padding-top:2px;flex-shrink:0}
.milestone-text{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--offwhite);line-height:1.6}

.chapter-image img{width:100%;height:280px;object-fit:cover;display:block}
.img-caption{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.05em;padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--light)}

.photo-strip{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px;background:var(--light);margin-top:2px}
.photo-strip.two-up{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}
.photo-strip.one-up{grid-template-columns:1fr}
.strip-item img{width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block}
.strip-item.wide img{height:260px}

.built-band{background:var(--navy);padding:80px 0;color:var(--offwhite)}
.built-band h2{font-size:clamp(28px,3vw,42px);color:var(--offwhite);margin-bottom:48px;font-weight:normal}
.built-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:48px}
.built-item{border-left:2px solid var(--gold);padding-left:24px}
.built-num{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.2em;color:var(--gold);display:block;margin-bottom:12px}
.built-item h4{font-size:17px;color:var(--offwhite);margin-bottom:10px;font-weight:normal}
.built-item p{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#94A3B8;line-height:1.7}

.work-cta{background:var(--gold);padding:64px 0}
.work-cta-inner{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:48px}
.work-cta .section-label{color:var(--navy);opacity:.7}
.work-cta .section-label::before{background:var(--navy);opacity:.4}
.work-cta h2{font-size:clamp(24px,3vw,38px);color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:12px;font-weight:normal}
.work-cta p{font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:var(--navy);opacity:.8;max-width:480px;line-height:1.7}
.cta-btn{background:var(--navy);color:var(--offwhite);padding:16px 32px;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;transition:background .2s;flex-shrink:0}
.cta-btn:hover{background:var(--slate)}

@media(max-width:900px){.chapter-body,.chapter-body.reverse{grid-template-columns:1fr;direction:ltr}.photo-strip{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.built-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.work-cta-inner{flex-direction:column}}
@media(max-width:768px){.photo-strip{grid-template-columns:1fr}.work-hero{padding:56px 0}.case-study{padding:56px 0}.built-band{padding:56px 0}.work-cta{padding:48px 0}}
</style>
